#1 Resected cecal adenocarcinoma with resection of liver metastasis
Prior to meeting with Mr. Lofton, I have had the opportunity to review his past medical records, laboratory tests, and imaging studies.  I have also had the opportunity to review this case in its entirety with Dr. Vasquez, my collaborating provider, who is in agreement with our plan.  Dr. Vasquez also was kind enough to visit with the patient directly.  After extensive discussion informing Mr. Lofton that we do not see any evidence of any disease recurrence, at this time have no data to support whether or not he should receive adjuvant therapy.  After an extensive discussion, it was decided that he would proceed with observation only with repeating imaging in approximately three-months' time at which time further discussion can be had regarding need for future treatment.  Patient states full understanding and agreement with this plan.  I am not making a formal return appointment due to the fact that patient is going to be following-up with his local provider.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

[end section id="20112"]

